Dear Zeren,

Thanks for getting in touch - Wouter mentioned that you would be working with the lulcc package.

In fact there is no need to create a data file like pie.rda - this is just a way of storing data within the package itself. In the demo code you will see the command:

lu <- DiscreteLulcRasterStack(x=stack(pie[1:3], ...))

The 'stack(...)' command creates a RasterStack object, which is supplied by the raster package (https://cran.r-project.org/web/packages/raster/index.html), which is the basis for many of the data classes in lulcc.

Taking the example of your two maps, you could do something like:

library(raster)
peru2000 = raster(
